Remington 'Remi' Walden was killed in March 2012 when his family's Jeep Grand Cherokee was rear-ended by a pickup truck in Georgia . 
  He was killed when the SUV exploded in flames after a fuel tank leaked from the rear of the vehicle . 
  Jurors in Georgia ruled that Chrysler acted with reckless disregard for human life in selling the family a 1999 Jeep with a gas tank mounted behind the rear axle . 
  Walden, of Bainbridge, Georgia, died when the Jeep driven by his aunt was hit from behind by a truck in 2012 . 
  The family has been awarded $150 million by a jury . 
 